5611 
5612 bool llvm::isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(const Instruction *I) {
5613  // Note: An atomic operation isn't guaranteed to return in a reasonable amount
5614  // of time because it's possible for another thread to interfere with it for an
5615  // arbitrary length of time, but programs aren't allowed to rely on that.
5616 
5617  // If there is no successor, then execution can't transfer to it.
5618  if (isa<ReturnInst>(I))
5619  return false;
5620  if (isa<UnreachableInst>(I))
5621  return false;
5622 
5623  // Note: Do not add new checks here; instead, change Instruction::mayThrow or
5624  // Instruction::willReturn.
5625  //
5626  // FIXME: Move this check into Instruction::willReturn.
5627  if (isa<CatchPadInst>(I)) {
5628  switch (classifyEHPersonality(I->getFunction()->getPersonalityFn())) {
5629  default:
5630  // A catchpad may invoke exception object constructors and such, which
5631  // in some languages can be arbitrary code, so be conservative by default.
5632  return false;
5633  case EHPersonality::CoreCLR:
5634  // For CoreCLR, it just involves a type test.
5635  return true;
5636  }
5637  }
5638 
5639  // An instruction that returns without throwing must transfer control flow
5640  // to a successor.
5641  return !I->mayThrow() && I->willReturn();
5642 }
5643 
5644 bool llvm::isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(const BasicBlock *BB) {
5645  // TODO: This is slightly conservative for invoke instruction since exiting
5646  // via an exception *is* normal control for them.
5647  for (const Instruction &I : *BB)
5648  if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&I))
5649  return false;
5650  return true;
5651 }
5652 
5653 bool llvm::isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(
5654  BasicBlock::const_iterator Begin, BasicBlock::const_iterator End,
5655  unsigned ScanLimit) {
5656  return isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(make_range(Begin, End),
5657  ScanLimit);
5658 }
5659 
5660 bool llvm::isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(
5661  iterator_range<BasicBlock::const_iterator> Range, unsigned ScanLimit) {
5662  assert(ScanLimit && "scan limit must be non-zero");
5663  for (const Instruction &I : Range) {
5664  if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I))
5665  continue;
5666  if (--ScanLimit == 0)
5667  return false;
5668  if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&I))
5669  return false;
5670  }
5671  return true;
5672 }
5673 
5674 bool llvm::isGuaranteedToExecuteForEveryIteration(const Instruction *I,
5675  const Loop *L) {
5676  // The loop header is guaranteed to be executed for every iteration.
5677  //
5678  // FIXME: Relax this constraint to cover all basic blocks that are
5679  // guaranteed to be executed at every iteration.
5680  if (I->getParent() != L->getHeader()) return false;
5681 
5682  for (const Instruction &LI : *L->getHeader()) {
5683  if (&LI == I) return true;
5684  if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&LI)) return false;
5685  }
5686  llvm_unreachable("Instruction not contained in its own parent basic block.");
5687 }
5688 
5689 bool llvm::propagatesPoison(const Use &PoisonOp) {
5690  const Operator *I = cast<Operator>(PoisonOp.getUser());
5691  switch (I->getOpcode()) {
5692  case Instruction::Freeze:
5693  case Instruction::PHI:
5694  case Instruction::Invoke:
5695  return false;
5696  case Instruction::Select:
5697  return PoisonOp.getOperandNo() == 0;
5698  case Instruction::Call:
5699  if (auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(I)) {
5700  switch (II->getIntrinsicID()) {
5701  // TODO: Add more intrinsics.
5702  case Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow:
5703  case Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow:
5704  case Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow:
5705  case Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow:
5706  case Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow:
5707  case Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow:
5708  // If an input is a vector containing a poison element, the
5709  // two output vectors (calculated results, overflow bits)'
5710  // corresponding lanes are poison.
5711  return true;
5712  case Intrinsic::ctpop:
5713  return true;
5714  }
5715  }
5716  return false;
5717  case Instruction::ICmp:
5718  case Instruction::FCmp:
5719  case Instruction::GetElementPtr:
5720  return true;
5721  default:
5722  if (isa<BinaryOperator>(I) || isa<UnaryOperator>(I) || isa<CastInst>(I))
5723  return true;
5724 
5725  // Be conservative and return false.
5726  return false;
5727  }
5728 }
5729 
5730 void llvm::getGuaranteedWellDefinedOps(
5731  const Instruction *I, SmallVectorImpl<const Value *> &Operands) {
5732  switch (I->getOpcode()) {
5733  case Instruction::Store:
5734  Operands.push_back(cast<StoreInst>(I)->getPointerOperand());
5735  break;
5736 
5737  case Instruction::Load:
5738  Operands.push_back(cast<LoadInst>(I)->getPointerOperand());
5739  break;
5740 
5741  // Since dereferenceable attribute imply noundef, atomic operations
5742  // also implicitly have noundef pointers too
5743  case Instruction::AtomicCmpXchg:
5744  Operands.push_back(cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I)->getPointerOperand());
5745  break;
5746 
5747  case Instruction::AtomicRMW:
5748  Operands.push_back(cast<AtomicRMWInst>(I)->getPointerOperand());
5749  break;
5750 
5751  case Instruction::Call:
5752  case Instruction::Invoke: {
5753  const CallBase *CB = cast<CallBase>(I);
5754  if (CB->isIndirectCall())
5755  Operands.push_back(CB->getCalledOperand());
5756  for (unsigned i = 0; i < CB->arg_size(); ++i) {
5757  if (CB->paramHasAttr(i, Attribute::NoUndef) ||
5758  CB->paramHasAttr(i, Attribute::Dereferenceable))
5759  Operands.push_back(CB->getArgOperand(i));
5760  }
5761  break;
5762  }
5763  case Instruction::Ret:
5764  if (I->getFunction()->hasRetAttribute(Attribute::NoUndef))
5765  Operands.push_back(I->getOperand(0));
5766  break;
5767  case Instruction::Switch:
5768  Operands.push_back(cast<SwitchInst>(I)->getCondition());
5769  break;
5770  case Instruction::Br: {
5771  auto *BR = cast<BranchInst>(I);
5772  if (BR->isConditional())
5773  Operands.push_back(BR->getCondition());
5774  break;
5775  }
5776  default:
5777  break;
5778  }
5779 }
5780 
5781 void llvm::getGuaranteedNonPoisonOps(const Instruction *I,
5782  SmallVectorImpl<const Value *> &Operands) {
5783  getGuaranteedWellDefinedOps(I, Operands);
5784  switch (I->getOpcode()) {
5785  // Divisors of these operations are allowed to be partially undef.
5786  case Instruction::UDiv:
5787  case Instruction::SDiv:
5788  case Instruction::URem:
5789  case Instruction::SRem:
5790  Operands.push_back(I->getOperand(1));
5791  break;
5792  default:
5793  break;
5794  }
5795 }
5796 
5797 bool llvm::mustTriggerUB(const Instruction *I,
5798  const SmallSet<const Value *, 16>& KnownPoison) {
5799  SmallVector<const Value *, 4> NonPoisonOps;
5800  getGuaranteedNonPoisonOps(I, NonPoisonOps);
5801 
5802  for (const auto *V : NonPoisonOps)
5803  if (KnownPoison.count(V))
5804  return true;
5805 
5806  return false;
5807 }
5808 
5809 static bool programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(const Value *V,
5810  bool PoisonOnly) {
5811  // We currently only look for uses of values within the same basic
5812  // block, as that makes it easier to guarantee that the uses will be
5813  // executed given that Inst is executed.
5814  //
5815  // FIXME: Expand this to consider uses beyond the same basic block. To do
5816  // this, look out for the distinction between post-dominance and strong
5817  // post-dominance.
5818  const BasicBlock *BB = nullptr;
5819  BasicBlock::const_iterator Begin;
5820  if (const auto *Inst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
5821  BB = Inst->getParent();
5822  Begin = Inst->getIterator();
5823  Begin++;
5824  } else if (const auto *Arg = dyn_cast<Argument>(V)) {
5825  BB = &Arg->getParent()->getEntryBlock();
5826  Begin = BB->begin();
5827  } else {
5828  return false;
5829  }
5830 
5831  // Limit number of instructions we look at, to avoid scanning through large
5832  // blocks. The current limit is chosen arbitrarily.
5833  unsigned ScanLimit = 32;
5834  BasicBlock::const_iterator End = BB->end();
5835 
5836  if (!PoisonOnly) {
5837  // Since undef does not propagate eagerly, be conservative & just check
5838  // whether a value is directly passed to an instruction that must take
5839  // well-defined operands.
5840 
5841  for (const auto &I : make_range(Begin, End)) {
5842  if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I))
5843  continue;
5844  if (--ScanLimit == 0)
5845  break;
5846 
5847  SmallVector<const Value *, 4> WellDefinedOps;
5848  getGuaranteedWellDefinedOps(&I, WellDefinedOps);
5849  if (is_contained(WellDefinedOps, V))
5850  return true;
5851 
5852  if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&I))
5853  break;
5854  }
5855  return false;
5856  }
5857 
5858  // Set of instructions that we have proved will yield poison if Inst
5859  // does.
5860  SmallSet<const Value *, 16> YieldsPoison;
5861  SmallSet<const BasicBlock *, 4> Visited;
5862 
5863  YieldsPoison.insert(V);
5864  Visited.insert(BB);
5865 
5866  while (true) {
5867  for (const auto &I : make_range(Begin, End)) {
5868  if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I))
5869  continue;
5870  if (--ScanLimit == 0)
5871  return false;
5872  if (mustTriggerUB(&I, YieldsPoison))
5873  return true;
5874  if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&I))
5875  return false;
5876 
5877  // If an operand is poison and propagates it, mark I as yielding poison.
5878  for (const Use &Op : I.operands()) {
5879  if (YieldsPoison.count(Op) && propagatesPoison(Op)) {
5880  YieldsPoison.insert(&I);
5881  break;
5882  }
5883  }
5884  }
5885 
5886  BB = BB->getSingleSuccessor();
5887  if (!BB || !Visited.insert(BB).second)
5888  break;
5889 
5890  Begin = BB->getFirstNonPHI()->getIterator();
5891  End = BB->end();
5892  }
5893  return false;
5894 }
5895 
5896 bool llvm::programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(const Instruction *Inst) {
5897  return ::programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(Inst, false);
5898 }
5899 
5900 bool llvm::programUndefinedIfPoison(const Instruction *Inst) {
5901  return ::programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(Inst, true);
5902 }
5903 
5904 static bool isKnownNonNaN(const Value *V, FastMathFlags FMF) {
5905  if (FMF.noNaNs())
5906  return true;
5907 
5908  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(V))
5909  return !C->isNaN();
5910 
5911  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantDataVector>(V)) {
5912  if (!C->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy())
5913  return false;
5914  for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getNumElements(); I < E; ++I) {
5915  if (C->getElementAsAPFloat(I).isNaN())
5916  return false;
5917  }
5918  return true;
5919  }
5920 
5921  if (isa<ConstantAggregateZero>(V))
5922  return true;
5923 
5924  return false;
5925 }
5926 
5927 static bool isKnownNonZero(const Value *V) {
5928  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(V))
5929  return !C->isZero();
5930 
5931  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantDataVector>(V)) {
5932  if (!C->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy())
5933  return false;
5934  for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getNumElements(); I < E; ++I) {
5935  if (C->getElementAsAPFloat(I).isZero())
5936  return false;
5937  }
5938  return true;
5939  }
5940 
5941  return false;
5942 }
5943 
5944 /// Match clamp pattern for float types without care about NaNs or signed zeros.
5945 /// Given non-min/max outer cmp/select from the clamp pattern this
5946 /// function recognizes if it can be substitued by a "canonical" min/max
5947 /// pattern.
5948 static SelectPatternResult matchFastFloatClamp(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
5949  Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
5950  Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
5951  Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS) {
5952  // Try to match
5953  // X < C1 ? C1 : Min(X, C2) --> Max(C1, Min(X, C2))
5954  // X > C1 ? C1 : Max(X, C2) --> Min(C1, Max(X, C2))
5955  // and return description of the outer Max/Min.
5956 
5957  // First, check if select has inverse order:
5958  if (CmpRHS == FalseVal) {
5959  std::swap(TrueVal, FalseVal);
5960  Pred = CmpInst::getInversePredicate(Pred);
5961  }
5962 
5963  // Assume success now. If there's no match, callers should not use these anyway.
5964  LHS = TrueVal;
5965  RHS = FalseVal;
5966 
5967  const APFloat *FC1;
5968  if (CmpRHS != TrueVal || !match(CmpRHS, m_APFloat(FC1)) || !FC1->isFinite())
5969  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5970 
5971  const APFloat *FC2;
5972  switch (Pred) {
5973  case CmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
5974  case CmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
5975  case CmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
5976  case CmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
5977  if (match(FalseVal,
5978  m_CombineOr(m_OrdFMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)),
5979  m_UnordFMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)))) &&
5980  *FC1 < *FC2)
5981  return {SPF_FMAXNUM, SPNB_RETURNS_ANY, false};
5982  break;
5983  case CmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
5984  case CmpInst::FCMP_OGE:
5985  case CmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
5986  case CmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
5987  if (match(FalseVal,
5988  m_CombineOr(m_OrdFMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)),
5989  m_UnordFMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)))) &&
5990  *FC1 > *FC2)
5991  return {SPF_FMINNUM, SPNB_RETURNS_ANY, false};
5992  break;
5993  default:
5994  break;
5995  }
5996 
5997  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5998 }
5999 
6000 /// Recognize variations of:
6001 /// CLAMP(v,l,h) ==> ((v) < (l) ? (l) : ((v) > (h) ? (h) : (v)))
6002 static SelectPatternResult matchClamp(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
6003  Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
6004  Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal) {
6005  // Swap the select operands and predicate to match the patterns below.
6006  if (CmpRHS != TrueVal) {
6007  Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
6008  std::swap(TrueVal, FalseVal);
6009  }
6010  const APInt *C1;
6011  if (CmpRHS == TrueVal && match(CmpRHS, m_APInt(C1))) {
6012  const APInt *C2;
6013  // (X <s C1) ? C1 : SMIN(X, C2) ==> SMAX(SMIN(X, C2), C1)
6014  if (match(FalseVal, m_SMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
6015  C1->slt(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT)
6016  return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
6017 
6018  // (X >s C1) ? C1 : SMAX(X, C2) ==> SMIN(SMAX(X, C2), C1)
6019  if (match(FalseVal, m_SMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
6020  C1->sgt(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT)
6021  return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
6022 
6023  // (X <u C1) ? C1 : UMIN(X, C2) ==> UMAX(UMIN(X, C2), C1)
6024  if (match(FalseVal, m_UMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
6025  C1->ult(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
6026  return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
6027 
6028  // (X >u C1) ? C1 : UMAX(X, C2) ==> UMIN(UMAX(X, C2), C1)
6029  if (match(FalseVal, m_UMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
6030  C1->ugt(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
6031  return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
6032  }
6033  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6034 }
6035 
6036 /// Recognize variations of:
6037 /// a < c ? min(a,b) : min(b,c) ==> min(min(a,b),min(b,c))
6038 static SelectPatternResult matchMinMaxOfMinMax(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
6039  Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
6040  Value *TVal, Value *FVal,
6041  unsigned Depth) {
6042  // TODO: Allow FP min/max with nnan/nsz.
6043  assert(CmpInst::isIntPredicate(Pred) && "Expected integer comparison");
6044 
6045  Value *A = nullptr, *B = nullptr;
6046  SelectPatternResult L = matchSelectPattern(TVal, A, B, nullptr, Depth + 1);
6047  if (!SelectPatternResult::isMinOrMax(L.Flavor))
6048  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6049 
6050  Value *C = nullptr, *D = nullptr;
6051  SelectPatternResult R = matchSelectPattern(FVal, C, D, nullptr, Depth + 1);
6052  if (L.Flavor != R.Flavor)
6053  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6054 
6055  // We have something like: x Pred y ? min(a, b) : min(c, d).
6056  // Try to match the compare to the min/max operations of the select operands.
6057  // First, make sure we have the right compare predicate.
6058  switch (L.Flavor) {
6059  case SPF_SMIN:
6060  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE) {
6061  Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
6062  std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
6063  }
6064  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE)
6065  break;
6066  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6067  case SPF_SMAX:
6068  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE) {
6069  Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
6070  std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
6071  }
6072  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE)
6073  break;
6074  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6075  case SPF_UMIN:
6076  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE) {
6077  Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
6078  std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
6079  }
6080  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
6081  break;
6082  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6083  case SPF_UMAX:
6084  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE) {
6085  Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
6086  std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
6087  }
6088  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
6089  break;
6090  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6091  default:
6092  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6093  }
6094 
6095  // If there is a common operand in the already matched min/max and the other
6096  // min/max operands match the compare operands (either directly or inverted),
6097  // then this is min/max of the same flavor.
6098 
6099  // a pred c ? m(a, b) : m(c, b) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, b))
6100  // ~c pred ~a ? m(a, b) : m(c, b) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, b))
6101  if (D == B) {
6102  if ((CmpLHS == A && CmpRHS == C) || (match(C, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
6103  match(A, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
6104  return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
6105  }
6106  // a pred d ? m(a, b) : m(b, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(b, d))
6107  // ~d pred ~a ? m(a, b) : m(b, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(b, d))
6108  if (C == B) {
6109  if ((CmpLHS == A && CmpRHS == D) || (match(D, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
6110  match(A, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
6111  return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
6112  }
6113  // b pred c ? m(a, b) : m(c, a) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, a))
6114  // ~c pred ~b ? m(a, b) : m(c, a) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, a))
6115  if (D == A) {
6116  if ((CmpLHS == B && CmpRHS == C) || (match(C, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
6117  match(B, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
6118  return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
6119  }
6120  // b pred d ? m(a, b) : m(a, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(a, d))
6121  // ~d pred ~b ? m(a, b) : m(a, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(a, d))
6122  if (C == A) {
6123  if ((CmpLHS == B && CmpRHS == D) || (match(D, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
6124  match(B, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
6125  return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
6126  }
6127 
6128  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6129 }
6130 
6131 /// If the input value is the result of a 'not' op, constant integer, or vector
6132 /// splat of a constant integer, return the bitwise-not source value.
6133 /// TODO: This could be extended to handle non-splat vector integer constants.
6134 static Value *getNotValue(Value *V) {
6135  Value *NotV;
6136  if (match(V, m_Not(m_Value(NotV))))
6137  return NotV;
6138 
6139  const APInt *C;
6140  if (match(V, m_APInt(C)))
6141  return ConstantInt::get(V->getType(), ~(*C));
6142 
6143  return nullptr;
6144 }
6145 
6146 /// Match non-obvious integer minimum and maximum sequences.
6147 static SelectPatternResult matchMinMax(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
6148  Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
6149  Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
6150  Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
6151  unsigned Depth) {
6152  // Assume success. If there's no match, callers should not use these anyway.
6153  LHS = TrueVal;
6154  RHS = FalseVal;
6155 
6156  SelectPatternResult SPR = matchClamp(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal);
6157  if (SPR.Flavor != SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_UNKNOWN)
6158  return SPR;
6159 
6160  SPR = matchMinMaxOfMinMax(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal, Depth);
6161  if (SPR.Flavor != SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_UNKNOWN)
6162  return SPR;
6163 
6164  // Look through 'not' ops to find disguised min/max.
6165  // (X > Y) ? ~X : ~Y ==> (~X < ~Y) ? ~X : ~Y ==> MIN(~X, ~Y)
6166  // (X < Y) ? ~X : ~Y ==> (~X > ~Y) ? ~X : ~Y ==> MAX(~X, ~Y)
6167  if (CmpLHS == getNotValue(TrueVal) && CmpRHS == getNotValue(FalseVal)) {
6168  switch (Pred) {
6169  case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT: return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
6170  case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT: return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
6171  case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT: return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
6172  case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT: return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
6173  default: break;
6174  }
6175  }
6176 
6177  // (X > Y) ? ~Y : ~X ==> (~X < ~Y) ? ~Y : ~X ==> MAX(~Y, ~X)
6178  // (X < Y) ? ~Y : ~X ==> (~X > ~Y) ? ~Y : ~X ==> MIN(~Y, ~X)
6179  if (CmpLHS == getNotValue(FalseVal) && CmpRHS == getNotValue(TrueVal)) {
6180  switch (Pred) {
6181  case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT: return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
6182  case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT: return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
6183  case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT: return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
6184  case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT: return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
6185  default: break;
6186  }
6187  }
6188 
6189  if (Pred != CmpInst::ICMP_SGT && Pred != CmpInst::ICMP_SLT)
6190  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6191 
6192  const APInt *C1;
6193  if (!match(CmpRHS, m_APInt(C1)))
6194  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6195 
6196  // An unsigned min/max can be written with a signed compare.
6197  const APInt *C2;
6198  if ((CmpLHS == TrueVal && match(FalseVal, m_APInt(C2))) ||
6199  (CmpLHS == FalseVal && match(TrueVal, m_APInt(C2)))) {
6200  // Is the sign bit set?
6201  // (X <s 0) ? X : MAXVAL ==> (X >u MAXVAL) ? X : MAXVAL ==> UMAX
6202  // (X <s 0) ? MAXVAL : X ==> (X >u MAXVAL) ? MAXVAL : X ==> UMIN
6203  if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT && C1->isZero() && C2->isMaxSignedValue())
6204  return {CmpLHS == TrueVal ? SPF_UMAX : SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
6205 
6206  // Is the sign bit clear?
6207  // (X >s -1) ? MINVAL : X ==> (X <u MINVAL) ? MINVAL : X ==> UMAX
6208  // (X >s -1) ? X : MINVAL ==> (X <u MINVAL) ? X : MINVAL ==> UMIN
6209  if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT && C1->isAllOnes() && C2->isMinSignedValue())
6210  return {CmpLHS == FalseVal ? SPF_UMAX : SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
6211  }
6212 
6213  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6214 }
6215 
6216 bool llvm::isKnownNegation(const Value *X, const Value *Y, bool NeedNSW) {
6217  assert(X && Y && "Invalid operand");
6218 
6219  // X = sub (0, Y) || X = sub nsw (0, Y)
6220  if ((!NeedNSW && match(X, m_Sub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(Y)))) ||
6221  (NeedNSW && match(X, m_NSWSub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(Y)))))
6222  return true;
6223 
6224  // Y = sub (0, X) || Y = sub nsw (0, X)
6225  if ((!NeedNSW && match(Y, m_Sub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(X)))) ||
6226  (NeedNSW && match(Y, m_NSWSub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(X)))))
6227  return true;
6228 
6229  // X = sub (A, B), Y = sub (B, A) || X = sub nsw (A, B), Y = sub nsw (B, A)
6230  Value *A, *B;
6231  return (!NeedNSW && (match(X, m_Sub(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
6232  match(Y, m_Sub(m_Specific(B), m_Specific(A))))) ||
6233  (NeedNSW && (match(X, m_NSWSub(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
6234  match(Y, m_NSWSub(m_Specific(B), m_Specific(A)))));
6235 }
6236 
6237 static SelectPatternResult matchSelectPattern(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
6238  FastMathFlags FMF,
6239  Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
6240  Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
6241  Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
6242  unsigned Depth) {
6243  bool HasMismatchedZeros = false;
6244  if (CmpInst::isFPPredicate(Pred)) {
6245  // IEEE-754 ignores the sign of 0.0 in comparisons. So if the select has one
6246  // 0.0 operand, set the compare's 0.0 operands to that same value for the
6247  // purpose of identifying min/max. Disregard vector constants with undefined
6248  // elements because those can not be back-propagated for analysis.
6249  Value *OutputZeroVal = nullptr;
6250  if (match(TrueVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) && !match(FalseVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) &&
6251  !cast<Constant>(TrueVal)->containsUndefOrPoisonElement())
6252  OutputZeroVal = TrueVal;
6253  else if (match(FalseVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) && !match(TrueVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) &&
6254  !cast<Constant>(FalseVal)->containsUndefOrPoisonElement())
6255  OutputZeroVal = FalseVal;
6256 
6257  if (OutputZeroVal) {
6258  if (match(CmpLHS, m_AnyZeroFP()) && CmpLHS != OutputZeroVal) {
6259  HasMismatchedZeros = true;
6260  CmpLHS = OutputZeroVal;
6261  }
6262  if (match(CmpRHS, m_AnyZeroFP()) && CmpRHS != OutputZeroVal) {
6263  HasMismatchedZeros = true;
6264  CmpRHS = OutputZeroVal;
6265  }
6266  }
6267  }
6268 
6269  LHS = CmpLHS;
6270  RHS = CmpRHS;
6271 
6272  // Signed zero may return inconsistent results between implementations.
6273  // (0.0 <= -0.0) ? 0.0 : -0.0 // Returns 0.0
6274  // minNum(0.0, -0.0) // May return -0.0 or 0.0 (IEEE 754-2008 5.3.1)
6275  // Therefore, we behave conservatively and only proceed if at least one of the
6276  // operands is known to not be zero or if we don't care about signed zero.
6277  switch (Pred) {
6278  default: break;
6279  case CmpInst::FCMP_OGT: case CmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
6280  case CmpInst::FCMP_UGT: case CmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
6281  if (!HasMismatchedZeros)
6282  break;
6283  [[fallthrough]];
6284  case CmpInst::FCMP_OGE: case CmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
6285  case CmpInst::FCMP_UGE: case CmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
6286  if (!FMF.noSignedZeros() && !isKnownNonZero(CmpLHS) &&
6287  !isKnownNonZero(CmpRHS))
6288  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6289  }
6290 
6291  SelectPatternNaNBehavior NaNBehavior = SPNB_NA;
6292  bool Ordered = false;
6293 
6294  // When given one NaN and one non-NaN input:
6295  // - maxnum/minnum (C99 fmaxf()/fminf()) return the non-NaN input.
6296  // - A simple C99 (a < b ? a : b) construction will return 'b' (as the
6297  // ordered comparison fails), which could be NaN or non-NaN.
6298  // so here we discover exactly what NaN behavior is required/accepted.
6299  if (CmpInst::isFPPredicate(Pred)) {
6300  bool LHSSafe = isKnownNonNaN(CmpLHS, FMF);
6301  bool RHSSafe = isKnownNonNaN(CmpRHS, FMF);
6302 
6303  if (LHSSafe && RHSSafe) {
6304  // Both operands are known non-NaN.
6305  NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_ANY;
6306  } else if (CmpInst::isOrdered(Pred)) {
6307  // An ordered comparison will return false when given a NaN, so it
6308  // returns the RHS.
6309  Ordered = true;
6310  if (LHSSafe)
6311  // LHS is non-NaN, so if RHS is NaN then NaN will be returned.
6312  NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_NAN;
6313  else if (RHSSafe)
6314  NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER;
6315  else
6316  // Completely unsafe.
6317  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6318  } else {
6319  Ordered = false;
6320  // An unordered comparison will return true when given a NaN, so it
6321  // returns the LHS.
6322  if (LHSSafe)
6323  // LHS is non-NaN, so if RHS is NaN then non-NaN will be returned.
6324  NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER;
6325  else if (RHSSafe)
6326  NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_NAN;
6327  else
6328  // Completely unsafe.
6329  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6330  }
6331  }
6332 
6333  if (TrueVal == CmpRHS && FalseVal == CmpLHS) {
6334  std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
6335  Pred = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
6336  if (NaNBehavior == SPNB_RETURNS_NAN)
6337  NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER;
6338  else if (NaNBehavior == SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER)
6339  NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_NAN;
6340  Ordered = !Ordered;
6341  }
6342 
6343  // ([if]cmp X, Y) ? X : Y
6344  if (TrueVal == CmpLHS && FalseVal == CmpRHS) {
6345  switch (Pred) {
6346  default: return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false}; // Equality.
6347  case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
6348  case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE: return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
6349  case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
6350  case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE: return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
6351  case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
6352  case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE: return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
6353  case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
6354  case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE: return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
6355  case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
6356  case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
6357  case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
6358  case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE: return {SPF_FMAXNUM, NaNBehavior, Ordered};
6359  case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
6360  case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
6361  case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
6362  case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE: return {SPF_FMINNUM, NaNBehavior, Ordered};
6363  }
6364  }
6365 
6366  if (isKnownNegation(TrueVal, FalseVal)) {
6367  // Sign-extending LHS does not change its sign, so TrueVal/FalseVal can
6368  // match against either LHS or sext(LHS).
6369  auto MaybeSExtCmpLHS =
6370  m_CombineOr(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_SExt(m_Specific(CmpLHS)));
6371  auto ZeroOrAllOnes = m_CombineOr(m_ZeroInt(), m_AllOnes());
6372  auto ZeroOrOne = m_CombineOr(m_ZeroInt(), m_One());
6373  if (match(TrueVal, MaybeSExtCmpLHS)) {
6374  // Set the return values. If the compare uses the negated value (-X >s 0),
6375  // swap the return values because the negated value is always 'RHS'.
6376  LHS = TrueVal;
6377  RHS = FalseVal;
6378  if (match(CmpLHS, m_Neg(m_Specific(FalseVal))))
6379  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
6380 
6381  // (X >s 0) ? X : -X or (X >s -1) ? X : -X --> ABS(X)
6382  // (-X >s 0) ? -X : X or (-X >s -1) ? -X : X --> ABS(X)
6383  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrAllOnes))
6384  return {SPF_ABS, SPNB_NA, false};
6385 
6386  // (X >=s 0) ? X : -X or (X >=s 1) ? X : -X --> ABS(X)
6387  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrOne))
6388  return {SPF_ABS, SPNB_NA, false};
6389 
6390  // (X <s 0) ? X : -X or (X <s 1) ? X : -X --> NABS(X)
6391  // (-X <s 0) ? -X : X or (-X <s 1) ? -X : X --> NABS(X)
6392  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrOne))
6393  return {SPF_NABS, SPNB_NA, false};
6394  }
6395  else if (match(FalseVal, MaybeSExtCmpLHS)) {
6396  // Set the return values. If the compare uses the negated value (-X >s 0),
6397  // swap the return values because the negated value is always 'RHS'.
6398  LHS = FalseVal;
6399  RHS = TrueVal;
6400  if (match(CmpLHS, m_Neg(m_Specific(TrueVal))))
6401  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
6402 
6403  // (X >s 0) ? -X : X or (X >s -1) ? -X : X --> NABS(X)
6404  // (-X >s 0) ? X : -X or (-X >s -1) ? X : -X --> NABS(X)
6405  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrAllOnes))
6406  return {SPF_NABS, SPNB_NA, false};
6407 
6408  // (X <s 0) ? -X : X or (X <s 1) ? -X : X --> ABS(X)
6409  // (-X <s 0) ? X : -X or (-X <s 1) ? X : -X --> ABS(X)
6410  if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrOne))
6411  return {SPF_ABS, SPNB_NA, false};
6412  }
6413  }
6414 
6415  if (CmpInst::isIntPredicate(Pred))
6416  return matchMinMax(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal, LHS, RHS, Depth);
6417 
6418  // According to (IEEE 754-2008 5.3.1), minNum(0.0, -0.0) and similar
6419  // may return either -0.0 or 0.0, so fcmp/select pair has stricter
6420  // semantics than minNum. Be conservative in such case.
6421  if (NaNBehavior != SPNB_RETURNS_ANY ||
6422  (!FMF.noSignedZeros() && !isKnownNonZero(CmpLHS) &&
6423  !isKnownNonZero(CmpRHS)))
6424  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6425 
6426  return matchFastFloatClamp(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal, LHS, RHS);
6427 }
6428 
6429 /// Helps to match a select pattern in case of a type mismatch.
6430 ///
6431 /// The function processes the case when type of true and false values of a
6432 /// select instruction differs from type of the cmp instruction operands because
6433 /// of a cast instruction. The function checks if it is legal to move the cast
6434 /// operation after "select". If yes, it returns the new second value of
6435 /// "select" (with the assumption that cast is moved):
6436 /// 1. As operand of cast instruction when both values of "select" are same cast
6437 /// instructions.
6438 /// 2. As restored constant (by applying reverse cast operation) when the first
6439 /// value of the "select" is a cast operation and the second value is a
6440 /// constant.
6441 /// NOTE: We return only the new second value because the first value could be
6442 /// accessed as operand of cast instruction.
6443 static Value *lookThroughCast(CmpInst *CmpI, Value *V1, Value *V2,
6444  Instruction::CastOps *CastOp) {
6445  auto *Cast1 = dyn_cast<CastInst>(V1);
6446  if (!Cast1)
6447  return nullptr;
6448 
6449  *CastOp = Cast1->getOpcode();
6450  Type *SrcTy = Cast1->getSrcTy();
6451  if (auto *Cast2 = dyn_cast<CastInst>(V2)) {
6452  // If V1 and V2 are both the same cast from the same type, look through V1.
6453  if (*CastOp == Cast2->getOpcode() && SrcTy == Cast2->getSrcTy())
6454  return Cast2->getOperand(0);
6455  return nullptr;
6456  }
6457 
6458  auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(V2);
6459  if (!C)
6460  return nullptr;
6461 
6462  Constant *CastedTo = nullptr;
6463  switch (*CastOp) {
6464  case Instruction::ZExt:
6465  if (CmpI->isUnsigned())
6466  CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, SrcTy);
6467  break;
6468  case Instruction::SExt:
6469  if (CmpI->isSigned())
6470  CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, SrcTy, true);
6471  break;
6472  case Instruction::Trunc:
6473  Constant *CmpConst;
6474  if (match(CmpI->getOperand(1), m_Constant(CmpConst)) &&
6475  CmpConst->getType() == SrcTy) {
6476  // Here we have the following case:
6477  //
6478  // %cond = cmp iN %x, CmpConst
6479  // %tr = trunc iN %x to iK
6480  // %narrowsel = select i1 %cond, iK %t, iK C
6481  //
6482  // We can always move trunc after select operation:
6483  //
6484  // %cond = cmp iN %x, CmpConst
6485  // %widesel = select i1 %cond, iN %x, iN CmpConst
6486  // %tr = trunc iN %widesel to iK
6487  //
6488  // Note that C could be extended in any way because we don't care about
6489  // upper bits after truncation. It can't be abs pattern, because it would
6490  // look like:
6491  //
6492  // select i1 %cond, x, -x.
6493  //
6494  // So only min/max pattern could be matched. Such match requires widened C
6495  // == CmpConst. That is why set widened C = CmpConst, condition trunc
6496  // CmpConst == C is checked below.
6497  CastedTo = CmpConst;
6498  } else {
6499  CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getIntegerCast(C, SrcTy, CmpI->isSigned());
6500  }
6501  break;
6502  case Instruction::FPTrunc:
6503  CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getFPExtend(C, SrcTy, true);
6504  break;
6505  case Instruction::FPExt:
6506  CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getFPTrunc(C, SrcTy, true);
6507  break;
6508  case Instruction::FPToUI:
6509  CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getUIToFP(C, SrcTy, true);
6510  break;
6511  case Instruction::FPToSI:
6512  CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getSIToFP(C, SrcTy, true);
6513  break;
6514  case Instruction::UIToFP:
6515  CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getFPToUI(C, SrcTy, true);
6516  break;
6517  case Instruction::SIToFP:
6518  CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getFPToSI(C, SrcTy, true);
6519  break;
6520  default:
6521  break;
6522  }
6523 
6524  if (!CastedTo)
6525  return nullptr;
6526 
6527  // Make sure the cast doesn't lose any information.
6528  Constant *CastedBack =
6529  ConstantExpr::getCast(*CastOp, CastedTo, C->getType(), true);
6530  if (CastedBack != C)
6531  return nullptr;
6532 
6533  return CastedTo;
6534 }
6535 
6536 SelectPatternResult llvm::matchSelectPattern(Value *V, Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
6537  Instruction::CastOps *CastOp,
6538  unsigned Depth) {
6539  if (Depth >= MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth)
6540  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6541 
6542  SelectInst *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(V);
6543  if (!SI) return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6544 
6545  CmpInst *CmpI = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(SI->getCondition());
6546  if (!CmpI) return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6547 
6548  Value *TrueVal = SI->getTrueValue();
6549  Value *FalseVal = SI->getFalseValue();
6550 
6551  return llvm::matchDecomposedSelectPattern(CmpI, TrueVal, FalseVal, LHS, RHS,
6552  CastOp, Depth);
6553 }
6554 
6555 SelectPatternResult llvm::matchDecomposedSelectPattern(
6556  CmpInst *CmpI, Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal, Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
6557  Instruction::CastOps *CastOp, unsigned Depth) {
6558  CmpInst::Predicate Pred = CmpI->getPredicate();
6559  Value *CmpLHS = CmpI->getOperand(0);
6560  Value *CmpRHS = CmpI->getOperand(1);
6561  FastMathFlags FMF;
6562  if (isa<FPMathOperator>(CmpI))
6563  FMF = CmpI->getFastMathFlags();
6564 
6565  // Bail out early.
6566  if (CmpI->isEquality())
6567  return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
6568 
6569  // Deal with type mismatches.
6570  if (CastOp && CmpLHS->getType() != TrueVal->getType()) {
6571  if (Value *C = lookThroughCast(CmpI, TrueVal, FalseVal, CastOp)) {
6572  // If this is a potential fmin/fmax with a cast to integer, then ignore
6573  // -0.0 because there is no corresponding integer value.
6574  if (*CastOp == Instruction::FPToSI || *CastOp == Instruction::FPToUI)
6575  FMF.setNoSignedZeros();
6576  return ::matchSelectPattern(Pred, FMF, CmpLHS, CmpRHS,
6577  cast<CastInst>(TrueVal)->getOperand(0), C,
6578  LHS, RHS, Depth);
6579  }
6580  if (Value *C = lookThroughCast(CmpI, FalseVal, TrueVal, CastOp)) {
6581  // If this is a potential fmin/fmax with a cast to integer, then ignore
6582  // -0.0 because there is no corresponding integer value.
6583  if (*CastOp == Instruction::FPToSI || *CastOp == Instruction::FPToUI)
6584  FMF.setNoSignedZeros();
6585  return ::matchSelectPattern(Pred, FMF, CmpLHS, CmpRHS,
6586  C, cast<CastInst>(FalseVal)->getOperand(0),
6587  LHS, RHS, Depth);
6588  }
6589  }
6590  return ::matchSelectPattern(Pred, FMF, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal,
6591  LHS, RHS, Depth);
6592 }
6593 
6594 CmpInst::Predicate llvm::getMinMaxPred(SelectPatternFlavor SPF, bool Ordered) {
6595  if (SPF == SPF_SMIN) return ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT;
6596  if (SPF == SPF_UMIN) return ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT;
6597  if (SPF == SPF_SMAX) return ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT;
6598  if (SPF == SPF_UMAX) return ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
6599  if (SPF == SPF_FMINNUM)
6600  return Ordered ? FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT : FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT;
6601  if (SPF == SPF_FMAXNUM)
6602  return Ordered ? FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT : FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT;
6603  llvm_unreachable("unhandled!");
6604 }
6605 
6606 SelectPatternFlavor llvm::getInverseMinMaxFlavor(SelectPatternFlavor SPF) {
6607  if (SPF == SPF_SMIN) return SPF_SMAX;
6608  if (SPF == SPF_UMIN) return SPF_UMAX;
6609  if (SPF == SPF_SMAX) return SPF_SMIN;
6610  if (SPF == SPF_UMAX) return SPF_UMIN;
6611  llvm_unreachable("unhandled!");
6612 }
6613 
6614 Intrinsic::ID llvm::getInverseMinMaxIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ID MinMaxID) {
6615  switch (MinMaxID) {
6616  case Intrinsic::smax: return Intrinsic::smin;
6617  case Intrinsic::smin: return Intrinsic::smax;
6618  case Intrinsic::umax: return Intrinsic::umin;
6619  case Intrinsic::umin: return Intrinsic::umax;
6620  default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected intrinsic");
6621  }
6622 }
6623 
6624 APInt llvm::getMinMaxLimit(SelectPatternFlavor SPF, unsigned BitWidth) {
6625  switch (SPF) {
6626  case SPF_SMAX: return APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth);
6627  case SPF_SMIN: return APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth);
6628  case SPF_UMAX: return APInt::getMaxValue(BitWidth);
6629  case SPF_UMIN: return APInt::getMinValue(BitWidth);
6630  default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected flavor");
6631  }
6632 }
6633 
6634 std::pair<Intrinsic::ID, bool>
6635 llvm::canConvertToMinOrMaxIntrinsic(ArrayRef<Value *> VL) {
6636  // Check if VL contains select instructions that can be folded into a min/max
6637  // vector intrinsic and return the intrinsic if it is possible.
6638  // TODO: Support floating point min/max.
6639  bool AllCmpSingleUse = true;
6640  SelectPatternResult SelectPattern;
6641  SelectPattern.Flavor = SPF_UNKNOWN;
6642  if (all_of(VL, [&SelectPattern, &AllCmpSingleUse](Value *I) {
6643  Value *LHS, *RHS;
6644  auto CurrentPattern = matchSelectPattern(I, LHS, RHS);
6645  if (!SelectPatternResult::isMinOrMax(CurrentPattern.Flavor) ||
6646  CurrentPattern.Flavor == SPF_FMINNUM ||
6647  CurrentPattern.Flavor == SPF_FMAXNUM ||
6648  !I->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy())
6649  return false;
6650  if (SelectPattern.Flavor != SPF_UNKNOWN &&
6651  SelectPattern.Flavor != CurrentPattern.Flavor)
6652  return false;
6653  SelectPattern = CurrentPattern;
6654  AllCmpSingleUse &=
6655  match(I, m_Select(m_OneUse(m_Value()), m_Value(), m_Value()));
6656  return true;
6657  })) {
6658  switch (SelectPattern.Flavor) {
6659  case SPF_SMIN:
6660  return {Intrinsic::smin, AllCmpSingleUse};
6661  case SPF_UMIN:
6662  return {Intrinsic::umin, AllCmpSingleUse};
6663  case SPF_SMAX:
6664  return {Intrinsic::smax, AllCmpSingleUse};
6665  case SPF_UMAX:
6666  return {Intrinsic::umax, AllCmpSingleUse};
6667  default:
6668  llvm_unreachable("unexpected select pattern flavor");
6669  }
6670  }
6671  return {Intrinsic::not_intrinsic, false};
6672 }
6673 
6674 bool llvm::matchSimpleRecurrence(const PHINode *P, BinaryOperator *&BO,
6675  Value *&Start, Value *&Step) {
6676  // Handle the case of a simple two-predecessor recurrence PHI.
6677  // There's a lot more that could theoretically be done here, but
6678  // this is sufficient to catch some interesting cases.
6679  if (P->getNumIncomingValues() != 2)
6680  return false;
6681 
6682  for (unsigned i = 0; i != 2; ++i) {
6683  Value *L = P->getIncomingValue(i);
6684  Value *R = P->getIncomingValue(!i);
6685  Operator *LU = dyn_cast<Operator>(L);
6686  if (!LU)
6687  continue;
6688  unsigned Opcode = LU->getOpcode();
6689 
6690  switch (Opcode) {
6691  default:
6692  continue;
6693  // TODO: Expand list -- xor, div, gep, uaddo, etc..
6694  case Instruction::LShr:
6695  case Instruction::AShr:
6696  case Instruction::Shl:
6697  case Instruction::Add:
6698  case Instruction::Sub:
6699  case Instruction::And:
6700  case Instruction::Or:
6701  case Instruction::Mul:
6702  case Instruction::FMul: {
6703  Value *LL = LU->getOperand(0);
6704  Value *LR = LU->getOperand(1);
6705  // Find a recurrence.
6706  if (LL == P)
6707  L = LR;
6708  else if (LR == P)
6709  L = LL;
6710  else
6711  continue; // Check for recurrence with L and R flipped.
6712 
6713  break; // Match!
6714  }
6715  };
6716 
6717  // We have matched a recurrence of the form:
6718  // %iv = [R, %entry], [%iv.next, %backedge]
6719  // %iv.next = binop %iv, L
6720  // OR
6721  // %iv = [R, %entry], [%iv.next, %backedge]
6722  // %iv.next = binop L, %iv
6723  BO = cast<BinaryOperator>(LU);
6724  Start = R;
6725  Step = L;
6726  return true;
6727  }
6728  return false;
6729 }
6730 
6731 bool llvm::matchSimpleRecurrence(const BinaryOperator *I, PHINode *&P,
6732  Value *&Start, Value *&Step) {
6733  BinaryOperator *BO = nullptr;
6734  P = dyn_cast<PHINode>(I->getOperand(0));
6735  if (!P)
6736  P = dyn_cast<PHINode>(I->getOperand(1));
6737  return P && matchSimpleRecurrence(P, BO, Start, Step) && BO == I;
6738 }
6739 
6740 /// Return true if "icmp Pred LHS RHS" is always true.
6741 static bool isTruePredicate(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, const Value *LHS,
6742  const Value *RHS, const DataLayout &DL,
6743  unsigned Depth) {
6744  if (ICmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred) && LHS == RHS)
6745  return true;
6746 
6747  switch (Pred) {
6748  default:
6749  return false;
6750 
6751  case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE: {
6752  const APInt *C;
6753 
6754  // LHS s<= LHS +_{nsw} C if C >= 0
6755  if (match(RHS, m_NSWAdd(m_Specific(LHS), m_APInt(C))))
6756  return !C->isNegative();
6757  return false;
6758  }
6759 
6760  case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE: {
6761  const APInt *C;
6762 
6763  // LHS u<= LHS +_{nuw} C for any C
6764  if (match(RHS, m_NUWAdd(m_Specific(LHS), m_APInt(C))))
6765  return true;
6766 
6767  // Match A to (X +_{nuw} CA) and B to (X +_{nuw} CB)
6768  auto MatchNUWAddsToSameValue = [&](const Value *A, const Value *B,
6769  const Value *&X,
6770  const APInt *&CA, const APInt *&CB) {
6771  if (match(A, m_NUWAdd(m_Value(X), m_APInt(CA))) &&
6772  match(B, m_NUWAdd(m_Specific(X), m_APInt(CB))))
6773  return true;
6774 
6775  // If X & C == 0 then (X | C) == X +_{nuw} C
6776  if (match(A, m_Or(m_Value(X), m_APInt(CA))) &&
6777  match(B, m_Or(m_Specific(X), m_APInt(CB)))) {
6778  KnownBits Known(CA->getBitWidth());
6779  computeKnownBits(X, Known, DL, Depth + 1, /*AC*/ nullptr,
6780  /*CxtI*/ nullptr, /*DT*/ nullptr);
6781  if (CA->isSubsetOf(Known.Zero) && CB->isSubsetOf(Known.Zero))
6782  return true;
6783  }
6784 
6785  return false;
6786  };
6787 
6788  const Value *X;
6789  const APInt *CLHS, *CRHS;
6790  if (MatchNUWAddsToSameValue(LHS, RHS, X, CLHS, CRHS))
6791  return CLHS->ule(*CRHS);
6792 
6793  return false;
6794  }
6795  }
6796 }
6797 
6798 /// Return true if "icmp Pred BLHS BRHS" is true whenever "icmp Pred
6799 /// ALHS ARHS" is true. Otherwise, return std::nullopt.
6800 static std::optional<bool>
6801 isImpliedCondOperands(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, const Value *ALHS,
6802  const Value *ARHS, const Value *BLHS, const Value *BRHS,
6803  const DataLayout &DL, unsigned Depth) {
6804  switch (Pred) {
6805  default:
6806  return std::nullopt;
6807 
6808  case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
6809  case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
6810  if (isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, BLHS, ALHS, DL, Depth) &&
6811  isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, ARHS, BRHS, DL, Depth))
6812  return true;
6813  return std::nullopt;
6814 
6815  case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
6816  case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
6817  if (isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, BLHS, ALHS, DL, Depth) &&
6818  isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, ARHS, BRHS, DL, Depth))
6819  return true;
6820  return std::nullopt;
6821  }
6822 }
6823 
6824 /// Return true if the operands of two compares (expanded as "L0 pred L1" and
6825 /// "R0 pred R1") match. IsSwappedOps is true when the operands match, but are
6826 /// swapped.
6827 static bool areMatchingOperands(const Value *L0, const Value *L1, const Value *R0,
6828  const Value *R1, bool &AreSwappedOps) {
6829  bool AreMatchingOps = (L0 == R0 && L1 == R1);
6830  AreSwappedOps = (L0 == R1 && L1 == R0);
6831  return AreMatchingOps || AreSwappedOps;
6832 }
6833 
6834 /// Return true if "icmp1 LPred X, Y" implies "icmp2 RPred X, Y" is true.
6835 /// Return false if "icmp1 LPred X, Y" implies "icmp2 RPred X, Y" is false.
6836 /// Otherwise, return std::nullopt if we can't infer anything.
6837 static std::optional<bool>
6838 isImpliedCondMatchingOperands(CmpInst::Predicate LPred,
6839  CmpInst::Predicate RPred, bool AreSwappedOps) {
6840  // Canonicalize the predicate as if the operands were not commuted.
6841  if (AreSwappedOps)
6842  RPred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(RPred);
6843 
6844  if (CmpInst::isImpliedTrueByMatchingCmp(LPred, RPred))
6845  return true;
6846  if (CmpInst::isImpliedFalseByMatchingCmp(LPred, RPred))
6847  return false;
6848 
6849  return std::nullopt;
6850 }
6851 
6852 /// Return true if "icmp LPred X, LC" implies "icmp RPred X, RC" is true.
6853 /// Return false if "icmp LPred X, LC" implies "icmp RPred X, RC" is false.
6854 /// Otherwise, return std::nullopt if we can't infer anything.
6855 static std::optional<bool> isImpliedCondCommonOperandWithConstants(
6856  CmpInst::Predicate LPred, const APInt &LC, CmpInst::Predicate RPred,
6857  const APInt &RC) {
6858  ConstantRange DomCR = ConstantRange::makeExactICmpRegion(LPred, LC);
6859  ConstantRange CR = ConstantRange::makeExactICmpRegion(RPred, RC);
6860  ConstantRange Intersection = DomCR.intersectWith(CR);
6861  ConstantRange Difference = DomCR.difference(CR);
6862  if (Intersection.isEmptySet())
6863  return false;
6864  if (Difference.isEmptySet())
6865  return true;
6866  return std::nullopt;
6867 }
6868 
6869 /// Return true if LHS implies RHS (expanded to its components as "R0 RPred R1")
6870 /// is true. Return false if LHS implies RHS is false. Otherwise, return
6871 /// std::nullopt if we can't infer anything.
6872 static std::optional<bool> isImpliedCondICmps(const ICmpInst *LHS,
6873  CmpInst::Predicate RPred,
6874  const Value *R0, const Value *R1,
6875  const DataLayout &DL,
6876  bool LHSIsTrue, unsigned Depth) {
6877  Value *L0 = LHS->getOperand(0);
6878  Value *L1 = LHS->getOperand(1);
6879 
6880  // The rest of the logic assumes the LHS condition is true. If that's not the
6881  // case, invert the predicate to make it so.
6882  CmpInst::Predicate LPred =
6883  LHSIsTrue ? LHS->getPredicate() : LHS->getInversePredicate();
6884 
6885  // Can we infer anything when the two compares have matching operands?
6886  bool AreSwappedOps;
6887  if (areMatchingOperands(L0, L1, R0, R1, AreSwappedOps))
6888  return isImpliedCondMatchingOperands(LPred, RPred, AreSwappedOps);
6889 
6890  // Can we infer anything when the 0-operands match and the 1-operands are
6891  // constants (not necessarily matching)?
6892  const APInt *LC, *RC;
6893  if (L0 == R0 && match(L1, m_APInt(LC)) && match(R1, m_APInt(RC)))
6894  return isImpliedCondCommonOperandWithConstants(LPred, *LC, RPred, *RC);
6895 
6896  if (LPred == RPred)
6897  return isImpliedCondOperands(LPred, L0, L1, R0, R1, DL, Depth);
6898 
6899  return std::nullopt;
6900 }
6901 
6902 /// Return true if LHS implies RHS is true. Return false if LHS implies RHS is
6903 /// false. Otherwise, return std::nullopt if we can't infer anything. We
6904 /// expect the RHS to be an icmp and the LHS to be an 'and', 'or', or a 'select'
6905 /// instruction.
6906 static std::optional<bool>
6907 isImpliedCondAndOr(const Instruction *LHS, CmpInst::Predicate RHSPred,
6908  const Value *RHSOp0, const Value *RHSOp1,
6909  const DataLayout &DL, bool LHSIsTrue, unsigned Depth) {
6910  // The LHS must be an 'or', 'and', or a 'select' instruction.
6911  assert((LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::And ||
6912  LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::Or ||
6913  LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::Select) &&
6914  "Expected LHS to be 'and', 'or', or 'select'.");
6915 
6916  assert(Depth <= MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth && "Hit recursion limit");
6917 
6918  // If the result of an 'or' is false, then we know both legs of the 'or' are
6919  // false. Similarly, if the result of an 'and' is true, then we know both
6920  // legs of the 'and' are true.
6921  const Value *ALHS, *ARHS;
6922  if ((!LHSIsTrue && match(LHS, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(ALHS), m_Value(ARHS)))) ||
6923  (LHSIsTrue && match(LHS, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(ALHS), m_Value(ARHS))))) {
6924  // FIXME: Make this non-recursion.
6925  if (std::optional<bool> Implication = isImpliedCondition(
6926  ALHS, RHSPred, RHSOp0, RHSOp1, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
6927  return Implication;
6928  if (std::optional<bool> Implication = isImpliedCondition(
6929  ARHS, RHSPred, RHSOp0, RHSOp1, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
6930  return Implication;
6931  return std::nullopt;
6932  }
6933  return std::nullopt;
6934 }
6935 
6936 std::optional<bool>
6937 llvm::isImpliedCondition(const Value *LHS, CmpInst::Predicate RHSPred,
6938  const Value *RHSOp0, const Value *RHSOp1,
6939  const DataLayout &DL, bool LHSIsTrue, unsigned Depth) {
6940  // Bail out when we hit the limit.
6941  if (Depth == MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth)
6942  return std::nullopt;
6943 
6944  // A mismatch occurs when we compare a scalar cmp to a vector cmp, for
6945  // example.
6946  if (RHSOp0->getType()->isVectorTy() != LHS->getType()->isVectorTy())
6947  return std::nullopt;
6948 
6949  assert(LHS->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) &&
6950  "Expected integer type only!");
6951 
6952  // Both LHS and RHS are icmps.
6953  const ICmpInst *LHSCmp = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(LHS);
6954  if (LHSCmp)
6955  return isImpliedCondICmps(LHSCmp, RHSPred, RHSOp0, RHSOp1, DL, LHSIsTrue,
6956  Depth);
6957 
6958  /// The LHS should be an 'or', 'and', or a 'select' instruction. We expect
6959  /// the RHS to be an icmp.
6960  /// FIXME: Add support for and/or/select on the RHS.
6961  if (const Instruction *LHSI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(LHS)) {
6962  if ((LHSI->getOpcode() == Instruction::And ||
6963  LHSI->getOpcode() == Instruction::Or ||
6964  LHSI->getOpcode() == Instruction::Select))
6965  return isImpliedCondAndOr(LHSI, RHSPred, RHSOp0, RHSOp1, DL, LHSIsTrue,
6966  Depth);
6967  }
6968  return std::nullopt;
6969 }
6970 
6971 std::optional<bool> llvm::isImpliedCondition(const Value *LHS, const Value *RHS,
6972  const DataLayout &DL,
6973  bool LHSIsTrue, unsigned Depth) {
6974  // LHS ==> RHS by definition
6975  if (LHS == RHS)
6976  return LHSIsTrue;
6977 
6978  if (const ICmpInst *RHSCmp = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(RHS))
6979  return isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHSCmp->getPredicate(),
6980  RHSCmp->getOperand(0), RHSCmp->getOperand(1), DL,
6981  LHSIsTrue, Depth);
6982 
6983  if (Depth == MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth)
6984  return std::nullopt;
6985 
6986  // LHS ==> (RHS1 || RHS2) if LHS ==> RHS1 or LHS ==> RHS2
6987  // LHS ==> !(RHS1 && RHS2) if LHS ==> !RHS1 or LHS ==> !RHS2
6988  const Value *RHS1, *RHS2;
6989  if (match(RHS, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(RHS1), m_Value(RHS2)))) {
6990  if (std::optional<bool> Imp =
6991  isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHS1, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
6992  if (*Imp == true)
6993  return true;
6994  if (std::optional<bool> Imp =
6995  isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHS2, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
6996  if (*Imp == true)
6997  return true;
6998  }
6999  if (match(RHS, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(RHS1), m_Value(RHS2)))) {
7000  if (std::optional<bool> Imp =
7001  isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHS1, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
7002  if (*Imp == false)
7003  return false;
7004  if (std::optional<bool> Imp =
7005  isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHS2, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
7006  if (*Imp == false)
7007  return false;
7008  }
7009 
7010  return std::nullopt;
7011 }
7012 
7013 // Returns a pair (Condition, ConditionIsTrue), where Condition is a branch
7014 // condition dominating ContextI or nullptr, if no condition is found.
7015 static std::pair<Value *, bool>
7016 getDomPredecessorCondition(const Instruction *ContextI) {
7017  if (!ContextI || !ContextI->getParent())
7018  return {nullptr, false};
7019 
7020  // TODO: This is a poor/cheap way to determine dominance. Should we use a
7021  // dominator tree (eg, from a SimplifyQuery) instead?
7022  const BasicBlock *ContextBB = ContextI->getParent();
7023  const BasicBlock *PredBB = ContextBB->getSinglePredecessor();
7024  if (!PredBB)
7025  return {nullptr, false};
7026 
7027  // We need a conditional branch in the predecessor.
7028  Value *PredCond;
7029  BasicBlock *TrueBB, *FalseBB;
7030  if (!match(PredBB->getTerminator(), m_Br(m_Value(PredCond), TrueBB, FalseBB)))
7031  return {nullptr, false};
7032 
7033  // The branch should get simplified. Don't bother simplifying this condition.
7034  if (TrueBB == FalseBB)
7035  return {nullptr, false};
7036 
7037  assert((TrueBB == ContextBB || FalseBB == ContextBB) &&
7038  "Predecessor block does not point to successor?");
7039 
7040  // Is this condition implied by the predecessor condition?
7041  return {PredCond, TrueBB == ContextBB};
7042 }
7043 
7044 std::optional<bool> llvm::isImpliedByDomCondition(const Value *Cond,
7045  const Instruction *ContextI,
7046  const DataLayout &DL) {
7047  assert(Cond->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) && "Condition must be bool");
7048  auto PredCond = getDomPredecessorCondition(ContextI);
7049  if (PredCond.first)
7050  return isImpliedCondition(PredCond.first, Cond, DL, PredCond.second);
7051  return std::nullopt;
7052 }
7053 
7054 std::optional<bool> llvm::isImpliedByDomCondition(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
7055  const Value *LHS,
7056  const Value *RHS,
7057  const Instruction *ContextI,
7058  const DataLayout &DL) {
7059  auto PredCond = getDomPredecessorCondition(ContextI);
7060  if (PredCond.first)
7061  return isImpliedCondition(PredCond.first, Pred, LHS, RHS, DL,
7062  PredCond.second);
7063  return std::nullopt;
7064 }
7065 
7066 static void setLimitsForBinOp(const BinaryOperator &BO, APInt &Lower,
7067  APInt &Upper, const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ,
7068  bool PreferSignedRange) {
7069  unsigned Width = Lower.getBitWidth();
7070  const APInt *C;
7071  switch (BO.getOpcode()) {
7072  case Instruction::Add:
7073  if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && !C->isZero()) {
7074  bool HasNSW = IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(&BO);
7075  bool HasNUW = IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(&BO);
7076 
7077  // If the caller expects a signed compare, then try to use a signed range.
7078  // Otherwise if both no-wraps are set, use the unsigned range because it
7079  // is never larger than the signed range. Example:
7080  // "add nuw nsw i8 X, -2" is unsigned [254,255] vs. signed [-128, 125].
7081  if (PreferSignedRange && HasNSW && HasNUW)
7082  HasNUW = false;
7083 
7084  if (HasNUW) {
7085  // 'add nuw x, C' produces [C, UINT_MAX].
7086  Lower = *C;
7087  } else if (HasNSW) {
7088  if (C->isNegative()) {
7089  // 'add nsw x, -C' produces [SINT_MIN, SINT_MAX - C].
7090  Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
7091  Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + *C + 1;
7092  } else {
7093  // 'add nsw x, +C' produces [SINT_MIN + C, SINT_MAX].
7094  Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + *C;
7095  Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
7096  }
7097  }
7098  }
7099  break;
7100 
7101  case Instruction::And:
7102  if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
7103  // 'and x, C' produces [0, C].
7104  Upper = *C + 1;
7105  break;
7106 
7107  case Instruction::Or:
7108  if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
7109  // 'or x, C' produces [C, UINT_MAX].
7110  Lower = *C;
7111  break;
7112 
7113  case Instruction::AShr:
7114  if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && C->ult(Width)) {
7115  // 'ashr x, C' produces [INT_MIN >> C, INT_MAX >> C].
7116  Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width).ashr(*C);
7117  Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width).ashr(*C) + 1;
7118  } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
7119  unsigned ShiftAmount = Width - 1;
7120  if (!C->isZero() && IIQ.isExact(&BO))
7121  ShiftAmount = C->countTrailingZeros();
7122  if (C->isNegative()) {
7123  // 'ashr C, x' produces [C, C >> (Width-1)]
7124  Lower = *C;
7125  Upper = C->ashr(ShiftAmount) + 1;
7126  } else {
7127  // 'ashr C, x' produces [C >> (Width-1), C]
7128  Lower = C->ashr(ShiftAmount);
7129  Upper = *C + 1;
7130  }
7131  }
7132  break;
7133 
7134  case Instruction::LShr:
7135  if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && C->ult(Width)) {
7136  // 'lshr x, C' produces [0, UINT_MAX >> C].
7137  Upper = APInt::getAllOnes(Width).lshr(*C) + 1;
7138  } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
7139  // 'lshr C, x' produces [C >> (Width-1), C].
7140  unsigned ShiftAmount = Width - 1;
7141  if (!C->isZero() && IIQ.isExact(&BO))
7142  ShiftAmount = C->countTrailingZeros();
7143  Lower = C->lshr(ShiftAmount);
7144  Upper = *C + 1;
7145  }
7146  break;
7147 
7148  case Instruction::Shl:
7149  if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
7150  if (IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(&BO)) {
7151  // 'shl nuw C, x' produces [C, C << CLZ(C)]
7152  Lower = *C;
7153  Upper = Lower.shl(Lower.countLeadingZeros()) + 1;
7154  } else if (BO.hasNoSignedWrap()) { // TODO: What if both nuw+nsw?
7155  if (C->isNegative()) {
7156  // 'shl nsw C, x' produces [C << CLO(C)-1, C]
7157  unsigned ShiftAmount = C->countLeadingOnes() - 1;
7158  Lower = C->shl(ShiftAmount);
7159  Upper = *C + 1;
7160  } else {
7161  // 'shl nsw C, x' produces [C, C << CLZ(C)-1]
7162  unsigned ShiftAmount = C->countLeadingZeros() - 1;
7163  Lower = *C;
7164  Upper = C->shl(ShiftAmount) + 1;
7165  }
7166  }
7167  }
7168  break;
7169 
7170  case Instruction::SDiv:
7171  if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
7172  APInt IntMin = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
7173  APInt IntMax = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width);
7174  if (C->isAllOnes()) {
7175  // 'sdiv x, -1' produces [INT_MIN + 1, INT_MAX]
7176  // where C != -1 and C != 0 and C != 1
7177  Lower = IntMin + 1;
7178  Upper = IntMax + 1;
7179  } else if (C->countLeadingZeros() < Width - 1) {
7180  // 'sdiv x, C' produces [INT_MIN / C, INT_MAX / C]
7181  // where C != -1 and C != 0 and C != 1
7182  Lower = IntMin.sdiv(*C);
7183  Upper = IntMax.sdiv(*C);
7184  if (Lower.sgt(Upper))
7185  std::swap(Lower, Upper);
7186  Upper = Upper + 1;
7187  assert(Upper != Lower && "Upper part of range has wrapped!");
7188  }
7189  } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
7190  if (C->isMinSignedValue()) {
7191  // 'sdiv INT_MIN, x' produces [INT_MIN, INT_MIN / -2].
7192  Lower = *C;
7193  Upper = Lower.lshr(1) + 1;
7194  } else {
7195  // 'sdiv C, x' produces [-|C|, |C|].
7196  Upper = C->abs() + 1;
7197  Lower = (-Upper) + 1;
7198  }
7199  }
7200  break;
7201 
7202  case Instruction::UDiv:
7203  if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && !C->isZero()) {
7204  // 'udiv x, C' produces [0, UINT_MAX / C].
7205  Upper = APInt::getMaxValue(Width).udiv(*C) + 1;
7206  } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
7207  // 'udiv C, x' produces [0, C].
7208  Upper = *C + 1;
7209  }
7210  break;
7211 
7212  case Instruction::SRem:
7213  if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
7214  // 'srem x, C' produces (-|C|, |C|).
7215  Upper = C->abs();
7216  Lower = (-Upper) + 1;
7217  }
7218  break;
7219 
7220  case Instruction::URem:
7221  if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
7222  // 'urem x, C' produces [0, C).
7223  Upper = *C;
7224  break;
7225 
7226  default:
7227  break;
7228  }
7229 }
7230 
7231 static void setLimitsForIntrinsic(const IntrinsicInst &II, APInt &Lower,
7232  APInt &Upper) {
7233  unsigned Width = Lower.getBitWidth();
7234  const APInt *C;
7235  switch (II.getIntrinsicID()) {
7236  case Intrinsic::ctpop:
7237  case Intrinsic::ctlz:
7238  case Intrinsic::cttz:
7239  // Maximum of set/clear bits is the bit width.
7240  assert(Lower == 0 && "Expected lower bound to be zero");
7241  Upper = Width + 1;
7242  break;
7243  case Intrinsic::uadd_sat:
7244  // uadd.sat(x, C) produces [C, UINT_MAX].
7245  if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)) ||
7246  match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
7247  Lower = *C;
7248  break;
7249  case Intrinsic::sadd_sat:
7250  if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)) ||
7251  match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
7252  if (C->isNegative()) {
7253  // sadd.sat(x, -C) produces [SINT_MIN, SINT_MAX + (-C)].
7254  Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
7255  Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + *C + 1;
7256  } else {
7257  // sadd.sat(x, +C) produces [SINT_MIN + C, SINT_MAX].
7258  Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + *C;
7259  Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
7260  }
7261  }
7262  break;
7263  case Intrinsic::usub_sat:
7264  // usub.sat(C, x) produces [0, C].
7265  if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)))
7266  Upper = *C + 1;
7267  // usub.sat(x, C) produces [0, UINT_MAX - C].
7268  else if (match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
7269  Upper = APInt::getMaxValue(Width) - *C + 1;
7270  break;
7271  case Intrinsic::ssub_sat:
7272  if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
7273  if (C->isNegative()) {
7274  // ssub.sat(-C, x) produces [SINT_MIN, -SINT_MIN + (-C)].
7275  Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
7276  Upper = *C - APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + 1;
7277  } else {
7278  // ssub.sat(+C, x) produces [-SINT_MAX + C, SINT_MAX].
7279  Lower = *C - APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width);
7280  Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
7281  }
7282  } else if (match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
7283  if (C->isNegative()) {
7284  // ssub.sat(x, -C) produces [SINT_MIN - (-C), SINT_MAX]:
7285  Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) - *C;
7286  Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
7287  } else {
7288  // ssub.sat(x, +C) produces [SINT_MIN, SINT_MAX - C].
7289  Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
7290  Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) - *C + 1;
7291  }
7292  }
7293  break;
7294  case Intrinsic::umin:
7295  case Intrinsic::umax:
7296  case Intrinsic::smin:
7297  case Intrinsic::smax:
7298  if (!match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)) &&
7299  !match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
7300  break;
7301 
7302  switch (II.getIntrinsicID()) {
7303  case Intrinsic::umin:
7304  Upper = *C + 1;
7305  break;
7306  case Intrinsic::umax:
7307  Lower = *C;
7308  break;
7309  case Intrinsic::smin:
7310  Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
7311  Upper = *C + 1;
7312  break;
7313  case Intrinsic::smax:
7314  Lower = *C;
7315  Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
7316  break;
7317  default:
7318  llvm_unreachable("Must be min/max intrinsic");
7319  }
7320  break;
7321  case Intrinsic::abs:
7322  // If abs of SIGNED_MIN is poison, then the result is [0..SIGNED_MAX],
7323  // otherwise it is [0..SIGNED_MIN], as -SIGNED_MIN == SIGNED_MIN.
7324  if (match(II.getOperand(1), m_One()))
7325  Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
7326  else
7327  Upper = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + 1;
7328  break;
7329  default:
7330  break;
7331  }
7332 }
7333 
7334 static void setLimitsForSelectPattern(const SelectInst &SI, APInt &Lower,
7335  APInt &Upper, const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ) {
7336  const Value *LHS = nullptr, *RHS = nullptr;
7337  SelectPatternResult R = matchSelectPattern(&SI, LHS, RHS);
7338  if (R.Flavor == SPF_UNKNOWN)
7339  return;
7340 
7341  unsigned BitWidth = SI.getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
7342 
7343  if (R.Flavor == SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_ABS) {
7344  // If the negation part of the abs (in RHS) has the NSW flag,
7345  // then the result of abs(X) is [0..SIGNED_MAX],
7346  // otherwise it is [0..SIGNED_MIN], as -SIGNED_MIN == SIGNED_MIN.
7347  Lower = APInt::getZero(BitWidth);
7348  if (match(RHS, m_Neg(m_Specific(LHS))) &&
7349  IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(cast<Instruction>(RHS)))
7350  Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth) + 1;
7351  else
7352  Upper = APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth) + 1;
7353  return;
7354  }
7355 
7356  if (R.Flavor == SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_NABS) {
7357  // The result of -abs(X) is <= 0.
7358  Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth);
7359  Upper = APInt(BitWidth, 1);
7360  return;
7361  }
7362 
7363  const APInt *C;
7364  if (!match(LHS, m_APInt(C)) && !match(RHS, m_APInt(C)))
7365  return;
7366 
7367  switch (R.Flavor) {
7368  case SPF_UMIN:
7369  Upper = *C + 1;
7370  break;
7371  case SPF_UMAX:
7372  Lower = *C;
7373  break;
7374  case SPF_SMIN:
7375  Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth);
7376  Upper = *C + 1;
7377  break;
7378  case SPF_SMAX:
7379  Lower = *C;
7380  Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth) + 1;
7381  break;
7382  default:
7383  break;
7384  }
7385 }
7386 
7387 static void setLimitForFPToI(const Instruction *I, APInt &Lower, APInt &Upper) {
7388  // The maximum representable value of a half is 65504. For floats the maximum
7389  // value is 3.4e38 which requires roughly 129 bits.
7390  unsigned BitWidth = I->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
7391  if (!I->getOperand(0)->getType()->getScalarType()->isHalfTy())
7392  return;
7393  if (isa<FPToSIInst>(I) && BitWidth >= 17) {
7394  Lower = APInt(BitWidth, -65504);
7395  Upper = APInt(BitWidth, 65505);
7396  }
7397 
7398  if (isa<FPToUIInst>(I) && BitWidth >= 16) {
7399  // For a fptoui the lower limit is left as 0.
7400  Upper = APInt(BitWidth, 65505);
7401  }
7402 }
7403 
7404 ConstantRange llvm::computeConstantRange(const Value *V, bool ForSigned,
7405  bool UseInstrInfo, AssumptionCache *AC,
7406  const Instruction *CtxI,
7407  const DominatorTree *DT,
7408  unsigned Depth) {
7409  assert(V->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && "Expected integer instruction");
7410 
7411  if (Depth == MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth)
7412  return ConstantRange::getFull(V->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits());
7413 
7414  const APInt *C;
7415  if (match(V, m_APInt(C)))
7416  return ConstantRange(*C);
7417 
7418  InstrInfoQuery IIQ(UseInstrInfo);
7419  unsigned BitWidth = V->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
7420  APInt Lower = APInt(BitWidth, 0);
7421  APInt Upper = APInt(BitWidth, 0);
7422  if (auto *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(V))
7423  setLimitsForBinOp(*BO, Lower, Upper, IIQ, ForSigned);
7424  else if (auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(V))
7425  setLimitsForIntrinsic(*II, Lower, Upper);
7426  else if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(V))
7427  setLimitsForSelectPattern(*SI, Lower, Upper, IIQ);
7428  else if (isa<FPToUIInst>(V) || isa<FPToSIInst>(V))
7429  setLimitForFPToI(cast<Instruction>(V), Lower, Upper);
7430 
7431  ConstantRange CR = ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(Lower, Upper);
7432 
7433  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V))
7434  if (auto *Range = IIQ.getMetadata(I, LLVMContext::MD_range))
7435  CR = CR.intersectWith(getConstantRangeFromMetadata(*Range));
7436 
7437  if (CtxI && AC) {
7438  // Try to restrict the range based on information from assumptions.
7439  for (auto &AssumeVH : AC->assumptionsFor(V)) {
7440  if (!AssumeVH)
7441  continue;
7442  IntrinsicInst *I = cast<IntrinsicInst>(AssumeVH);
7443  assert(I->getParent()->getParent() == CtxI->getParent()->getParent() &&
7444  "Got assumption for the wrong function!");
7445 
7446  if (!isValidAssumeForContext(I, CtxI, DT))
7447  continue;
7448  Value *Arg = I->getArgOperand(0);
7449  ICmpInst *Cmp = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(Arg);
7450  // Currently we just use information from comparisons.
7451  if (!Cmp || Cmp->getOperand(0) != V)
7452  continue;
7453  // TODO: Set "ForSigned" parameter via Cmp->isSigned()?
7454  ConstantRange RHS =
7455  computeConstantRange(Cmp->getOperand(1), /* ForSigned */ false,
7456  UseInstrInfo, AC, I, DT, Depth + 1);
7457  CR = CR.intersectWith(
7458  ConstantRange::makeAllowedICmpRegion(Cmp->getPredicate(), RHS));
7459  }
7460  }
7461 
7462  return CR;
7463 }
7464 
7465 static std::optional<int64_t>
7466 getOffsetFromIndex(const GEPOperator *GEP, unsigned Idx, const DataLayout &DL) {
7467  // Skip over the first indices.
7468  gep_type_iterator GTI = gep_type_begin(GEP);
7469  for (unsigned i = 1; i != Idx; ++i, ++GTI)
7470  /*skip along*/;
7471 
7472  // Compute the offset implied by the rest of the indices.
7473  int64_t Offset = 0;
7474  for (unsigned i = Idx, e = GEP->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i, ++GTI) {
7475  ConstantInt *OpC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(GEP->getOperand(i));
7476  if (!OpC)
7477  return std::nullopt;
7478  if (OpC->isZero())
7479  continue; // No offset.
7480 
7481  // Handle struct indices, which add their field offset to the pointer.
7482  if (StructType *STy = GTI.getStructTypeOrNull()) {
7483  Offset += DL.getStructLayout(STy)->getElementOffset(OpC->getZExtValue());
7484  continue;
7485  }
7486 
7487  // Otherwise, we have a sequential type like an array or fixed-length
7488  // vector. Multiply the index by the ElementSize.
7489  TypeSize Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(GTI.getIndexedType());
7490  if (Size.isScalable())
7491  return std::nullopt;
7492  Offset += Size.getFixedValue() * OpC->getSExtValue();
7493  }
7494 
7495  return Offset;
7496 }
7497 
7498 std::optional<int64_t> llvm::isPointerOffset(const Value *Ptr1,
7499  const Value *Ptr2,
7500  const DataLayout &DL) {
7501  APInt Offset1(DL.getIndexTypeSizeInBits(Ptr1->getType()), 0);
7502  APInt Offset2(DL.getIndexTypeSizeInBits(Ptr2->getType()), 0);
7503  Ptr1 = Ptr1->stripAndAccumulateConstantOffsets(DL, Offset1, true);
7504  Ptr2 = Ptr2->stripAndAccumulateConstantOffsets(DL, Offset2, true);
7505 
7506  // Handle the trivial case first.
7507  if (Ptr1 == Ptr2)
7508  return Offset2.getSExtValue() - Offset1.getSExtValue();
7509 
7510  const GEPOperator *GEP1 = dyn_cast<GEPOperator>(Ptr1);
7511  const GEPOperator *GEP2 = dyn_cast<GEPOperator>(Ptr2);
7512 
7513  // Right now we handle the case when Ptr1/Ptr2 are both GEPs with an identical
7514  // base. After that base, they may have some number of common (and
7515  // potentially variable) indices. After that they handle some constant
7516  // offset, which determines their offset from each other. At this point, we
7517  // handle no other case.
7518  if (!GEP1 || !GEP2 || GEP1->getOperand(0) != GEP2->getOperand(0) ||
7519  GEP1->getSourceElementType() != GEP2->getSourceElementType())
7520  return std::nullopt;
7521 
7522  // Skip any common indices and track the GEP types.
7523  unsigned Idx = 1;
7524  for (; Idx != GEP1->getNumOperands() && Idx != GEP2->getNumOperands(); ++Idx)
7525  if (GEP1->getOperand(Idx) != GEP2->getOperand(Idx))
7526  break;
7527 
7528  auto IOffset1 = getOffsetFromIndex(GEP1, Idx, DL);
7529  auto IOffset2 = getOffsetFromIndex(GEP2, Idx, DL);
7530  if (!IOffset1 || !IOffset2)
7531  return std::nullopt;
7532  return *IOffset2 - *IOffset1 + Offset2.getSExtValue() -
7533  Offset1.getSExtValue();
7534 }
